info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Red Flag Warning issued May 29 at 2:56PM CDT until May 29 at 8:00PM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...RED FLAG WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 PM CDT THIS EVENING FOR GUSTY SOUTHERLY WINDS AND VERY LOW RELATIVE HUMIDITY FOR CENTRAL AND NORTHERN ST. LOUIS COUNTY AND NORTHERN COOK AND NORTHERN LAKE COUNTIES... * AFFECTED AREA...In northeast Minnesota, central and northern St. Louis, northern Cook and northern Lake Counties. * WINDS...South around 10 to 15 mph with gusts up to 25 mph. * RELATIVE HUMIDITY...As low as 18 percent. * IMPACTS...Any fires may grow and spread quickly.
info.instruction: This Red Flag Warning means that critical fire weather conditions are expected through this evening. A combination of gusty southerly winds, low relative humidity, and warm temperatures can contribute to extreme fire behavior.
